Int'l Body for Study of Juche Idea and Songun Politics Formed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- An international alliance of East European and Central Asian societies for the study of the Juche idea and the Songun politics was formed with due ceremony in Sankt-Peterburg on September 5. The alliance groups ten organizations in eight countries and regions in East Europe and Central Asia.
 Attending the ceremony were leading officials and members of organizations for the study of the Juche idea and the Songun politics in Russia, Ukraine, Belarus, Moldova, Poland, Kazakhstan and other countries and regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory messages from the International Institute of the Juche Idea and the European Society for the Study of the Juche Idea were conveyed and a congratulatory address was made at the ceremony. Then, a report and speeches were made on such subjects as "Strategy and tactics of the International Alliance for East European and Central Asian Societies for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Songun Politics", "On the basic viewpoint based on the Juche idea and the Songun politics" and "Let's launch a struggle for independence under the banner of Songun, the line of independence".
 The reporter and speakers were unanimous in holding that the Juche idea and the Songun politics serve as the only guidelines to cope with the present situation in which the imperialists' high-handed practices, aggression and intervention are getting evermore pronounced. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed the importance of forming the above-said alliance and coordinating its actions and placing the study and dissemination of the Juche idea and the Songun politics on a more organized and positive basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mikhail Panchenko, chairman of the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Songun Politics, was elected general secretary of the alliance at the ceremony.
 The participants adopted the six-chapter statute of the alliance and decided to publish magazine "Banner of Songun" with a view to regularly informing the IIJI and organizations of the alliance of its activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to leader Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

Bolstering Revolutionary Armed Forces Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- The joint slogans issued by the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea on the occasion of its 60th birthday are significantly heightening the mettle of the Korean People's Army to win sure victory.
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a by-lined article. It goes on: 
 The Korean People's Army will fully embody the idea and spirit reflected in the joint slogans and demonstrate the spirit of the strong revolutionary army of Mt. Paektu to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans set it as the primary task for bolstering the military muscle to turn the whole army into the militant ranks devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One of the joint slogans is "Let the whole army wage the O Jung Hup-led 7th Regiment Movement forcefully to become the first death-defying corps and first human bullets and bombs in defending the headquarters of the revolution!" The joint slogans call for establishing the WPK's commanding system and revolutionary military discipline throughout the army and urge all the servicepersons to become the most ardent followers of the Songun idea, the most reliable defenders and creditable implementers of the idea. This fully represents the intention of the Party to develop the People's Army into the vanguard ranks protecting the headquarters of the revolution in the van.
 The People's Army is the army of the Party and the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The supreme mission of the People's Army as a driving force for revolution is to devotedly defend the leader. The worth of its existence would be unthinkable without the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA, the devoted protector of the leader, can strikingly demonstrate its mettle to win sure victory only when it implements to the letter the militant tasks laid down in the joint slogans. 
 The joint slogans clearly indicate ways of strengthening the People's Army into invincible revolutionary armed forces and firmly defending the sovereignty of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans include slogans calling upon all the servicepersons to prepare themselves as a-match-for-a hundred fighters, establish the steel-like military discipline throughout the army and significantly improve the appearance of the army as regular forces and give the fullest play to the mettle of the army so as to mete out severe and merciless punishment to the aggressors and the provokers in hearty response to the WPK's training-first policy. These slogans serve as a militant banner which the army should always hold aloft for increasing its combat capability. The thorough implementation of the joint slogans would help bolster the revolutionary armed forces.
 The People's Army is fully prepared as invincible armed forces capable of firmly protecting the sovereignty of the country and the nation. Unshakable is the determination of the army to shatter any provocations of the enemies and firmly protect the sovereignty of the country and the happiness of the people. 
 The KPA will thoroughly implement the militant tasks laid down in the joint slogans to powerfully demonstrate the might of the invincible revolutionary armed forces.

57th Birthday of DPRK Celebrated Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks and a film show were held in the Czech Republic, ceremonies of opening Korean book and handicraft exhibitions in Lima of Peru and Pitesti of Romania, a ceremony of opening a week of Korean photo exhibition in Abuja of Nigeria and a film show and a photo exhibition in Singapore of Singapore from Sep. 1 to 3 on the occasion of the 57th birthday of the DPRK. 
  On display were photos showing the revolutionary activities and famous works of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il and books, photos and handicrafts showing the development of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean films "'The Ever-Victorious Workers' Party of Korea', Gymnastic and Artistic Performance Celebrating the 55th Anniversary of the WPK" and "Great Leadership Leading the Building of a Great Prosperous Powerful Nation to Victory " were screened at the film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the functions were political, public and economic figures and people from all walks of life in those countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of a city committee of the Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia said that through the round-table talks and film show he came to know well about Korea and that the DPRK is a genuine people's government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The governor of a district of Lima of Peru hoped that the Korean people with a history of 5,000 years and one language and lineage would live in happiness in a reunified powerful country in the near future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Receptions, photo exhibitions, film shows and friendly meetings were held at the DPRK missions in Shenyang of China, Pakistan, Thailand, Indonesia, Syria, Singapore, Cambodia, Kuwait, Romania, Germany, the Czech Republic, Uganda, Guinea, Nigeria, South Africa, Democratic Congo, Brazil and Peru from Sept. 7 to 10 on the same occasion.

Vigilance against U.S. Attempt for Preemptive Nuclear Attack Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- A draft "doctrine for joint nuclear operation" was made public by the U.S. Department of Defense on Sept. 10. According to it, the field U.S. army commanders may request the U.S. president to allow the use of nuclear weapons in different "emergency cases" for mounting a preemptive attack on "enemy's" weapons of mass destruction, countering dangerous conventional weapons, putting an early end to war and the like. 
 Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed commentary. 
The U.S. intention to amend the doctrine under the pretext of what it calls "emergency" is a dangerous attempt to drastically widen the scope of using nuclear weapons and extremely reduce its limit and thus justify its preemptive use of nuclear weapons in any region and country in case of considering it necessary, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is intended to trample down with nuke upon those anti-U.S. independent countries which stand firm against its pressure and threat. It is the U.S. stereotype trick to accuse those countries disobedient to its words of "keeping weapons of mass destruction and "developing biological and chemical weapons" and make a military attack at random under this pretext. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is all the more serious is that the first target of the doctrine is none other than the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Clear is the ulterior intention of the U.S. talking about settlement of the nuclear issue through dialogue under the pretext of the six-party talks. In a word, it is to disarm the DPRK and stifle it with nuke. The U.S. attempt to amend the doctrine is a climax of its open nuclear threat and moves to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the DPRK stands squarely against any U.S. nuclear threat. It is fully ready to decisively control a preemptive nuclear attack with a strong retaliatory blow even if the U.S. commits it any moment. The DPRK is proud to see how wise it was that it has strengthened all its deterrent force in line with the Songun policy to cope with the U.S. moves for a nuclear preemptive attack against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK cannot remain indifferent towards the U.S. attempt at a preemptive nuclear attack and will steadily strengthen its war deterrent to defend national sovereignty and security with supreme vigilance.

Joint Slogans Praised as Banner of Struggle for Victory in Movement for National Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- The joint slogans released by the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the WPK represent the unshakable will of the WPK to lead the present era of independent reunification to victory, true to President Kim Il Sung's idea and line of national reunification, Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says in a signed article.
 The historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, a brilliant embodiment of the President's idea of independent reunification, solemnly declared at home and abroad that the issue of national reunification should be independently settled by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation, its master, the article says, and goes on:
 Since the adoption of the joint declaration, the Korean nation has conducted a vigorous movement for independent reunification in the idea of "By our nation itself" specified in the declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 World-startling events and wonderful successes in the inter-Korean relations and the movement for national reunification are a clear manifestation of the validity and vitality of the President's idea and line of independent reunification as they have been achieved thanks to the concerted struggle of the Korean nation  under the banner of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans have great vitality as they carry the firm will of the WPK to accomplish the cause of national reunification by carrying out  President's idea and line of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans serve as a weapon of struggle to remarkably stir up the patriotic enthusiasm of the Korean nation to achieve the reunification and independent development of the country in the noble idea of "By our nation itself".
 They called for building an independent, prosperous and powerful reunified country in the three thousand-ri land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The building of a reunified country guaranteeing the destiny of the country and bright future of the Korean nation in the new century is unthinkable apart from the energetic struggle of all the members of the Korean nation to vigorously advance the June 15 era for reunification.

National Computer Program Contest and Exhibition Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- The 16th national computer program contest and exhibition took place at the Three-Revolution Exhibition from Sept. 13 to 20.
 Exhibited there were more than 750 excellent programs presented by scientists, technicians and youth and students in the field of information science and technology from across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The contest and exhibition were divided into such panels as computerization of ministries and national institutions, competition of programs for stable operation of computers, mechanic translation program competition, exhibition of programs in wide use for production and management in different domains of the national economy and academic presentation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this period tens of thousands of people visited the exhibition and lectures were given on the trend of IT development and program products were exchanged.
 In the panel of computerization of ministries and national institutions the Ministry of Land and Marine Transport took a special place and the Ministry of Railways, the Ministry of Public Health, the Ministry of Forestry and the Bureau for Service to Foreigners came first. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the successful entrants were not a few units including the Academy of Sciences, Kim Il Sung University, Kim Chaek University of Technology and Kum Song School.
 A closing ceremony was held on Sept. 20. Among those present there were Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the results were announced by the jury of the contest and exhibition, pennants, medals and certificates were awarded to the successful units and participants and relevant prizes went to them.

Korean Women Model after Kim Jong Suk
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero and woman commander of Mt. Paektu, is the great paragon for the Korean women.
 She showed the spirit of defending the leader with her very life, revolutionary comradeship and great love for the rising generation. Her noble traits have served as a priceless heritage which all the Korean women should follow generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In an interview with KCNA, Pak Kum Ju, vice-director of a department of the Central Committee of the Korean Democratic Women's Union, said the women are striving hard to model after Kim Jong Suk so as to train themselves as female revolutionaries.
 Union members are holding study meetings and gatherings for expressing impressions on books dealing with her immortal exploits and other colorful activities for following her noble traits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such campaign proves effective in practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Kum Bok residing in Rakwon County and Sin Mun Ok in Hamhung City of South Hamgyong Province protected the portraits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu from natural disasters that hit their residential quarters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yu Chun Hwa in Orang County of North Hamgyong Province saved workers by shielding a stone rolling down at a power station construction site. Sin Hye Yong in Jongphyong County, South Hamgyong Province, pulled out a fellow's child from drowning ahead of her own one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 So Hye Suk in Pyongyang, Ri Hui Sun in North Hamgyong Province and Pak Myong Bok in South Phyongan Province are bringing up many orphans in their houses.
 This has become a social trait in the country.

Koryo Life-giving Water Generator
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 21 (KCNA) -- The Koryo life-giving water generator has been widely introduced in public health, catering and other fields and even in families in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. The demand for it is on a steady increase.
 The generator was developed by the Koryo Life-giving Water Technical Center under the Academy of Koryo Medical Science. It, with a special electrode, produces deoxidized water and oxidizing water with a strong sterilization power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are three sizes of generators,large, medium and small. The generator produces strong alkali, alkali, weak alkali water and strong acid and weak acid water according to uses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The production cost of the generator is cheap. Its electric consumption is low and the serviceable life of its electrode is six years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The generator converts piped water and spring water into deoxidized water and oxidizing water. The electric potential of the deoxidized water is 160 to -400mV; and that of the oxidizing water is 1,000-1,200 mV and its PH is strong acid. The former is available for drinking water and the latter for sterilizing water.
 The deoxidized water is efficacious for the prevention and treatment of the adult diseases and promotes the growth of children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The generator is available in prevention of aging, treatment of diseases and sanitation.
